# TriFrame: Assembly-Free Metagenomic Functional Annotation

TriFrame is a deep learning model that takes raw metagenomic DNA reads (150–300 bp) and directly predicts functional annotations — EC numbers, KEGG orthologs, and COG categories — without requiring assembly, ORF prediction, or database alignment. The key challenge is that a random metagenomic read could originate from any of six reading frames (3 forward + 3 reverse complement) and may not even be protein-coding. TriFrame addresses this with two novel architectural components: **Frame Attention with Gating**, which learns to identify the correct coding frame(s), and **Cross-Resolution Attention**, which fuses nucleotide-level compositional signals with codon-level protein function signals at different granularities.

## Architecture

```
                         DNA Read (150-300 bp)
                                │
                 ┌──────────────┴──────────────┐
                 ▼                              ▼
      ┌────────────────────┐        ┌────────────────────┐
      │ Nucleotide Encoder │        │ 6-Frame Translator  │
      │ (Dilated Conv1d)   │        │ (Deterministic)     │
      └────────┬───────────┘        └────────┬───────────┘
               │                              │
               │                    ┌─────────▼──────────┐
               │                    │   Frame Encoder     │
               │                    │ (Shared-weight TF)  │
               │                    └─────────┬──────────┘
               │                              │
               │                    ┌─────────▼──────────┐
               │                    │  Frame Attention    │  ← NOVEL
               │                    │  (Cross-frame +    │
               │                    │   Gating)          │
               │                    └─────────┬──────────┘
               │                              │
               └──────────┐    ┌──────────────┘
                          ▼    ▼
                ┌────────────────────┐
                │  Cross-Resolution  │  ← NOVEL
                │  Attention Fusion  │
                └────────┬───────────┘
                         │
              ┌──────────┼──────────┬──────────┐
              ▼          ▼          ▼          ▼
          ┌───────┐ ┌────────┐ ┌───────┐ ┌───────┐
          │Coding │ │  EC    │ │ KEGG  │ │  COG  │
          │/Frame │ │Numbers │ │  KO   │ │ Cat.  │
          └───────┘ └────────┘ └───────┘ └───────┘
```

## Model Configurations

| Config | d_nuc | d_frame | Nuc Layers | Frame Layers | Parameters |
|--------|-------|---------|------------|--------------|------------|
| Small  | 192   | 256     | 4          | 4            | ~11M       |
| Base   | 384   | 512     | 8          | 6            | ~56M       |
| Large  | 512   | 768     | 12         | 8            | ~162M      |

